(942, 161, '2015-12-17 05:40:20', '2015-12-17 05:40:20', '<p class="journal-inner"><span class="drop-cap">A</span>fter an off-road wine filled trip through the Chianti region of Italy (think Napa valley with hand made signs and no paved roads), the next GPS way point was set to Porto Venere; a small port city on the north west side of the “boot”.  Arriving in a tiny, but very “efficient”, cinquecento covered in Tuscan sand and dirt, I handed the Fiat to the valet driver whose skill is akin to fitting the square peg in the round hole.</p>\r\n<p class="journal-inner">I digress. Porto Venere is a place where no car is desired because it can be walked in a matter of hours. It''s a place where you actually connect with a local crowd, absent and drowned of heavy tourism and loud noises. With a beautiful uninterrupted view of multicolor hand painted buildings that touch the sea wall.  I was captured immediately and thrilled to be spending the weekend.</p>\r\n<p class="journal-inner">Aimlessly walking with my trusted partner *#TBT film Leica M6* I captured as much as I could.  They (<del>read Wikipedia</del>) say the name, Portovenere, comes from the goddess Venus where the church of Peter the Apostle now stands.</p>\r\n<p class="journal-inner">Walking up to the church is a little adventure and has some great detours (hint: bring your swimwear).  Just before reaching the top, you can go to the rock formed beach and relax on one of the ledges; or have a very daring (and cold) swim.  Joking aside, the views are spectacular. The rock formations in the middle of the ocean, the natural caves, and beautiful clear water make it the spot for locals to go and just <em>unwind</em>. Picture this; a simple church laid out in black and white stone with only natural light bouncing its true beauty and simplicity.</p>\r\n<p class="journal-inner">It left me with a final thought: When I have a daughter, she will be married here*</p>\r\n<img class="alignleft  wp-image-883" src="http://dev.hungrylemur.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/1077106069-2400x1590.jpg" alt="1077106069" width="409" height="271" />', 'THE HIDDEN "6th" LAND', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '888-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-12-17 05:40:20', '2015-12-17 05:40:20', '', 888, 'http://dev.hungrylemur.com/888-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
